Hello and welcome to Blue Sky, a modpack designed for the players. This is a kitchensink version of this pack and you can feel free to do whatever you like, or follow the qustbook if you desire.
Simply check the checkbox and be on you way.
We hope you have fun!!

To get anywhere int his pack, chop down your first tree.

Â§lMake sure to always keep a spare sapling.
After collecting alot of wood to craft and build with, craft the basics of your journey.
To increase the amount of saplings you recieve i suggest using a crook. You will also recieve some silkworms. Someone told me that they like to live in leaves of trees.

With a sieve you can gather basic resources from certain blocks, why not try all of them.
Just check the box when your ready.

To get more dirt use your barrel and put any living item inside such as saplings, appleas and silkworms.
Then simply sieve the dirt and get as much resources as possible, trust me you'll need them.

After sieving all taht dirt you would have got Stone Pebbles, craft these up to make cobblestone.
Then keep some cobblestone behind, and smash the rest into gravel with a good old hammer.

You will now need to sieve once again to get more valuable resources. 
But don't sieve all you gravel you will need to smash it into sand.
Time to seive you sand now but like all the rest save some because you'll need to smash it into dust
From sieving through the dust you gather some bones and gunpowder from dead creatures. Sounds nice.
After all you hard work from sieving you should have a metric ton of seeds if not, back to work you go :)

If you have sieved and gravel by now you should have realised there is a ton of materials you get. 
Gather them all!
Only one item from sieving sand, what a shame.

Were the resources come from i dont know, maybe the water Gods??
To setup up this contraption, you will need to make a steam and place the strainer base under a flowing water block then place the strainer on top. 
Warning nets do not last forever they need replaced.
All those pieces you have gathered can be turned to chunks and smelted in a regular vanilla furnace but i would wait.

We all know of the tinkers smeltery but the best thing bout it is that it doubles your chunks. 
Now that you have access to sand, gravel and clay you can make grout.

You are going to need lava to fuel your smeltery.
First you will need to get a crucible and a heat source for under it. Throw some cobblestone inside and now you have lava.

With the smeltery you can create alot of alloys including obsidian.
Get a bucket of water and lava and click the smeltery drain, it will go in and you can pour out obsidian.
Or you can use the stone barrel method and put lava in the barrel and water on top.
This is a very dangerous place be carefull and dont die.

Useing diffrent meshes can have a big impact on what you get from sieving.
Its up to you to figure out what you need.
You will need to make a mobfarm for some basic materials, build one as soon as possible
Since you have access to grass seeds yo can make a passive mob farm for food and resources.
This mod adds fantastic and cool multiblocks which can process items and generate RF

The coke even can generate coke and creosote oil from coal or logs. 
From the creosote oil you can make treated wood which is used throughout the mod
The blast furnace generates steel from iron and coke.
Adding 9 steel sheetmetal and preheaters the speed of the oven is improved
With one extra hopper, power and preheaters the speed of the furnace is improved
You can make alloys in this multiblock by supplying it with fuel.
Low voltage power trasmisson
Medium voltage power trasmission
High voltage power trasmisson
Simple generation from water, try to make it as effective as possible
Power generation from the wind. You can add windmill sails to it to make them more effective.
Now you can generate power from heat, simply place a cold and hot block directly opposite on this block and it will start generating power.
This mechanism allows you to build multiblocks in a very easy way. No need to remember anymore.
A block that lets your create multiblocks
A block that lets your create multiblocks
A block that lets your create multiblocks
Blueprints allows you to create items that cant be crafted in normal vanilla.
This is like Immersive Engineering's own crafting table.
The garden cloche is a powwerful block that when fuelled with power and water can grow crops at a fast rate.
The metal press is a multiblock that allows you to press into metals to get diffrent outcomes like gears and plates.
Throughout this mod you will need a wrench to rotate and pickup blocks
This is the same as a vanilla furnace but it uses power and can be given upgrades while being very configurable
As in the name this block will break down items into a dust.
The sawmill saws down wood and gives you out more than you would if you simply crafted planks, it will also give out bi-products
The induction smelter combines two items into something new, like alloying two metals.
The phtogenic Insolator is like farming in a block, with the use of phyto-gro you can mutiply plants.

To get this material, place TNT down somewhere safe and throw some iron on it, then light the tnt up and watch as compressed iron is created.
Note there is a 20% chance you iron will be destroyed.

To compress air you will need the following blocks to create and move it into machines.
Note - Pressure tubes can explode if the pressure is too high thats why there are modules which help regulate the tubes, i suggest using them.
The steam dynamo uses water and a burnable item to create RF
The compression dynamo needs fluid fuel and coolants to create RF
The reactant dynamo needs fluid fuel and a solid to create RF
This dynamo requires thermal currency
The magma crucible boils up items into their liquid form.
The enervation dynamo removes RF from items
The fractionating still seperates a liquid useing power into another liquid and sometimes a bi-product
The fluid transposer will allow you to fill items up with fluid such as ducts.
The magmatic dynamo uses hot fluids to to create RF
The energetic infuser allows you to charge certain items up with RF such as a battery.
The igneous extruder allows you to make cobblestone, stone and obsidian from water and lava.
The arcane ensorcellator will allow you to make enchants from items and experience

Thermal Mods adds alot of ways to transport items, fluid, energy and people.
Â§cÂ§cRemember all these items can be upgraded into better versions.

Thermal satchels allow you to carry items around in a comapact way.
Â§cRemember all these items can be upgraded into better versions.

Flux capacitors are portable way to move RF rather tha ducts.
Â§cRemember all these items can be upgraded into better versions.

Thermal has alot of items that allow you to extract, insert, retrieve and send signals through ducts.
Â§cRemember all these items can be upgraded into better versions.

These useful items allow you to move liquids portably without using buckets.
Â§cRemember all these items can be upgraded into better versions.
The pressure chamber has two uses, it can pressurize air and pump it out or it can pressurize items like compressed iron instead of using tnt.

You need to make plastic to move on so you need oil, you can do this from immersive engineering. Go to the immersive engineering tab to find out. 
So firstly you will need to put 4 refinerys on top of each other. Then put 4 vortex tubes next to block of xompressed iron which are next to the refinerys, make sure the hot side is attached to the block on the cold side place a heat sinks on them. Then pump presurized air into the vortex tubes. Now oil should seperate in them.

This is a long and grindy process which has alot of explaining. JEI will help.
Firstly toy need to make an empty PCB this is made is the pressure chamber. Put the empty PCB in the UV light box this will take a while without speed upgrades. You will get another empty PCB but the tooltip said it has 100% to etch. This means you throw it in Etching acid for 5 minutes, this will turn it into a unassembled PCB. Now you will need to do alot of pressure chamber crafting to make a printed circuit board which is used for the next machines.

To get liquid plastic you will need to pump lpg and a piece of coal into thermophneumatic proccesing plant. You will then need to pump the plastic into the plastic mixer with dyes to get the colour of palstic you need.
This tablet is awesome it acts as a villager trading system. Simply charge your tablet up and have the price item in a nearby chest and watch the magic happen.

This multiblock structure (kind of) will allow you to craete certain items.
You will need certain assembly programs which you can get from the Tablet. You will need to setup all these machines around the assembly platform and a chest for input and outputs. There is 2 assembly io's, if you click one with a pneumatic wrench it will turn blue. You only need to put pressure into the controller.

This blocks will make pressure generation and movement alot more effecient and easier.
Use the tooltips.
These 2 hoppers are very usefull in moving liquids and items.
These 2 items will allow you to convert between RF and Pressure.
You will need to craft these block and items to start actually additions
Crates are amazing, far better than chests
These are the basic machines of AA use them to your advantage. You can generate power and reconstruct items.
With the powered furnace and crusher you can automate ore processing or any other purpose you want it for.
With these blocks you can automate alot of things and make you life alot simplier.

Oil can be used to generate power and to also make plastic in pneumaticraft, so don't use all of it.
To get oil you will first need to find a chunk with oil in it with the core sample drill, then setup a pump jack in that chunk (use the projector and manual). Then pump the oil into a distillation tower (multiblock) and it will seperate it into diffrent liquids. Use them to your advantage.
Refined uranium is the fuel for Extreme Reactors, to get it just smelt down some yellorium chunks. You will need alot of it so make extras.

Reactors are multiblocks that provide power. You will need to place coolant blocks or fluids around you fuel rods to havve best effeciency, there is a list of them on the big reactor wiki.
Only attach your coolant port when your going to make a turbine.

Turbines are multiblocks that need a reactor to start with. Build your turbine then remove a block from your reactor and place the coolant port there, pump water into your reactor, then it will craete steam: the steam then needs pumped into the turbine for it to work.

To start this pack you will need to go through Ex Nihilo Creatio and Compressum.
